com.tealium.collect

Class TealiumCollect

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tealium.collect.TealiumCollect

  • public final class TealiumCollect
extends java.lang.Object
    Main class for this TealiumCollect library.

    enable(TealiumCollect.Config) must be called before using any of the other methods.

    • Method Detail

      • getEventListeners

        public static java.util.Collection<java.util.EventListener> getEventListeners()
        Add an EventListener to receive profile update events.

        The EventListeners that receive events are:

        • TealiumCollect.OnAudienceUpdateListener
        • TealiumCollect.OnBadgeUpdateListener
        • TealiumCollect.OnFlagUpdateListener
        • TealiumCollect.OnDateUpdateListener
        • TealiumCollect.OnMetricUpdateListener
        • TealiumCollect.OnPropertyUpdateListener
        • TealiumCollect.OnProfileUpdatedListener

      • isEnabled

        public static boolean isEnabled()
        Returns:
        Whether the Tealium Collect library is enabled (enable(Config) has been called).

      • enable

        public static void enable(TealiumCollect.Config config)
        Initialize the library with the desired configuration.
        Parameters:
        config - a Config instance. If null or the library is already initialized, a warning will be logged in LogCat and the call will have no effect.

      • disable

        public static void disable()
        Disable the initialized library. If the library was not initialized this call has no effect.

      • sendEvent

        public static void sendEvent(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,?> data)
        Send an event dispatch to Tealium Collect. This method calls send(String, Map) with the first argument as "link" along with the given data.
        Parameters:
        data - the data tied to this event. The values provided by the map are copied into Strings, org.json.JSONArrays, and org.json.JSONObjects depending on their original type.
